1. Single Inheritance
      you will create one object for one class and that's same object can access the another class 

 #example
 #in the given program one object is created for son class that same son object is can access the dad class if you put like this:
    class dad():
    def phone(self):       
        print("Dads phone")
    
class son(dad):          #in this place we put dad class in son class so son object can access the dad class.means the son can access the dad class
    def laptop(self):
        print("son's laptop")

aravinth=son()     #you create a separate object for son
aravinth.laptop()  
aravinth.phone()        #son's laptop
