2. Multiple Inheritance
       in this you will create one object for one class that's same object can access another 2 classes

 #example
 #in the given program one object is created for son class and that son object will access the dad and mom classes 

 class dad():
    def phone(self):
        print("Dads phone")
class mom():
    def food(self):
        print("Moms food")
    
class son(dad,mom):       #in this place we put a dad and mom classes in inside of son class.means the son can be access the mom and dad classes
    def laptop(self):
        print("son's laptop")

aravinth=son()     #you create a separate object for son
aravinth.laptop()  
aravinth.phone()    # 
aravinth.food()

3.Multilevel inheritance
   #in this one object created for 'dad' class that  object will connected to 'grandpa' class.so the 'grandpa' will be acccess by the 'dad' class
   #in this another object is created for 'son' class class that object will connect to 'dad' class.so the 'son' class can access both 'dad' and 'grandpa'because the dad class was connected to the gradpa class

class grandpa():
    def phone(self):
        print("grandpa's phone")
        
class dad(grandpa):        #we put grandpa class in inside of dad class so grandpa class will be access by the dad class
    def money(self):
        print("Dads money")

    
class son(dad):     #we put 'dad' class in inside of 'son' class so both 'dad' and 'grandpa' class will be access by the 'son' class
    def laptop(self):
        print("son's laptop")

aravinth=son()      #son object
aravinth.laptop()  
aravinth.money()     

jacob=dad()     #dad object
jacob.phone()        #son's laptop
                     Dads money
                    grandpa's phone

